    ('EAS-E 114', 'DINOSAURS AND THEIR RELATIVES', '13185', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 11:35 AM–12:25 PM', 'GY 1045', 'P. David Polly', 4, 'Lecture', 'Lecture', '3', 'GEOLOGICAL SCIENCES', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Origin and evolution of vertebrates including dinosaurs and their distant relatives, such as fish, amphibians, birds and mammals. Course will focus on dinosaur evolution, paleobiology, paleoecology, and extinction. The scientific method, and quantitative and qualitative methodologies will be presented. Two lectures and one demonstration each week.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd N&M credit - Natural Science
