    ('EAS-E 121', 'ORIGIN AND EVOLUTION OF MARS AND ROCKY PLANETARY BODIES', '12857', 'Closed', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 12:45 PM–2:00 PM', 'GY 2049', 'Juergen Schieber', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'GEOLOGICAL SCIENCES', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Our current understanding of Mars is derived from the study of meteorites, lunar samples, geology, space probes, and landed rovers. Geological processes that are operative on Earth are also operative on Mars and similar planetary bodies, but differing boundary conditions have generated distinct outcomes. These differences have implications for the likelihood of finding life on Mars.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd N&M credit - Natural Science
COLL (CASE) N&M Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('EAS-E 141', 'EARTHQUAKES AND VOLCANOES', '29294', 'Closed', 'Tu Tuesday 12:45 PM–2:45 PM', 'GY 2029', 'Jianhua Gong', 0, 'Laboratory', 'Laboratory', '3', 'GEOLOGICAL SCIENCES', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Examination of the causes and effects of earthquakes and volcanic activity. Impacts of earthquakes and volcanic eruptions, including secondary effects such as landslides, mudflows, and tsunamis; climatic effects; energy/mineral resources; and social disruption. Mitigation of effects of natural disasters.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd N&M credit - Natural Science
COLL (CASE) N&M Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
