    ('EAS-E 225', 'EARTH MATERIALS', '7852', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 11:10 AM–12:25 PM', 'GY 2064', 'Shelby Rader', 0, 'Lecture', 'Lecture', '4', 'GEOLOGICAL SCIENCES', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'This course considers sequentially minerals, rocks, sediments and soils; the materials the comprise the solid earth. The distribution and environmental significance of these materials are studied, as are their chemical and physical interactions with groundwater and plants. Three 50-minute lectures and one 2-hour laboratory per week. Laboratory attendance is required.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) N&M Breadth of Inquiry credit
Class uses IU eTexts'], NULL),
