    ('ECON-E 115', 'EVERYDAY ECONOMICS', '7056', 'Closed', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 2:20 PM–3:35 PM', 'TH A201', 'Todd Walker', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'LEE NORVELLE THEATRE DRAMA/ NE', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Establishes the foundation necessary to achieve economic literacy by providing an introduction to economic concepts and institutions encountered in daily life: credit markets, inflation, interest rates, taxes, retirement savings, insurance, and the fundamental economic principles underlying these markets. Cannot be counted toward a major, interdepartmental major, or minor in economics.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd S&H credit
COLL (CASE) S&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 211', 'APPLIED PRINCIPLES OF MICROECONOMICS: CREATIVE COMMERCE', '8985', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 12:45 PM–2:00 PM', 'GA 1112', 'Gerhard Glomm', 22, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'GLOBAL & INTERNATIONAL STUDIES', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Introduction to core microeconomic principles with applications to creative commerce. Covers scarcity, opportunity cost, competitive and non-competitive market pricing, as well as topics like supply chain management, branding, advertising and special behavioral features including snob effects, bandwagon effects, and particular search/shopping behavior for experience vs search goods.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) S&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 251', 'FUNDAMENTALS OF ECONOMICS I', '9525', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 9:35 AM–10:50 AM', 'BH 013', 'James Self', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'BALLANTINE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'First course in a two-course sequence that lays the foundations for a solid understanding of economics. Examines the economic notions of cost and gains from trade, determinants of economic growth, consumer and firm behavior in competitive and non-competitive environments, the effects of taxation, externalities, moral hazard and adverse selection, and public policy applications.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) S&H Breadth of Inquiry credit
Class uses IU eTexts'], NULL),
