Class uses IU eTexts'], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 371', 'INTRODUCTION TO APPLIED ECONOMETRICS', '6920', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 9:35 AM–10:50 AM', 'GA 0003', 'Bo Hu', 1, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'GLOBAL & INTERNATIONAL STUDIES', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'An introduction to the theory and application of least-squares regression in empirical economics. Review of bivariate and multivariate regression models, hypothesis testing, and confidence intervals. Special topics include model specification, multicollinearity, heteroscedasticity, dummy variables, interactions, and various sources of estimation bias. Students will learn to work with both cross-sectional and time-series datasets, and analyze the data using an econometrics software package.', ARRAY['Class uses IU eTexts'], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 371', 'INTRODUCTION TO APPLIED ECONOMETRICS', '15144', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 2:20 PM–3:35 PM', 'HH 2049', 'Robert Lantis', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'GLOBAL & INTERNATIONAL STUDIES', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'An introduction to the theory and application of least-squares regression in empirical economics. Review of bivariate and multivariate regression models, hypothesis testing, and confidence intervals. Special topics include model specification, multicollinearity, heteroscedasticity, dummy variables, interactions, and various sources of estimation bias. Students will learn to work with both cross-sectional and time-series datasets, and analyze the data using an econometrics software package.', ARRAY['Class uses IU eTexts'], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 401', 'MACHINE LEARNING FOR ECONOMIC DATA', '11507', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 8:00 AM–9:15 AM', 'BH 005', 'Yuki Ito', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'BALLANTINE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'What is machine learning and how can we use it to help us explore economic data? This course develops exploratory data analysis skills and provides training in a variety of machine learning techniques used to analyze economic data while using the R programming language.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 425', 'FINANCIAL ECONOMICS', '6921', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 2:20 PM–3:35 PM', 'WY 005', 'Robert Becker', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'WYLIE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Theory and empirical evidence relevant to understanding the functioning of modern financial-asset markets. Course topics may vary substantially by instructor. Some examples include: present value, analysis of risk and return, asset pricing, modern portfolio theory, equilibrium in asset markets, arbitrage pricing theory, the capital asset pricing model, the efficient markets hypothesis, price bubbles and crashes, futures markets, derivative securities and option pricing models.', ARRAY['Class uses IU eTexts'], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 471', 'ECONOMETRIC THEORY AND PRACTICE I', '9378', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 12:45 PM–2:00 PM', 'WY 329', 'Bo Hu', 3, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'WYLIE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Emphasis is on the classical linear regression model and its applications. Special topics include finite and asymptotic properties of least squares, hypothesis testing, model specification, dummy variables, proxies, multicollinearity and heteroscedasticity.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 490', 'ADVANCED UNDERGRADUATE SEMINAR IN ECONOMICS', '30541', 'Class Status', 'F Friday 2:15 PM–4:45 PM', 'WY 015', 'Ahmad Lashkaripour', 1, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'WYLIE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Advanced intensive study of a topic area in economics. Topics will vary.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 490', 'ADVANCED UNDERGRADUATE SEMINAR IN ECONOMICS', '37071', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 11:10 AM–12:25 PM', 'WY 329', 'Daniela Valdivia', 10, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'WYLIE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Advanced intensive study of a topic area in economics. Topics will vary.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 490', 'ADVANCED UNDERGRADUATE SEMINAR IN ECONOMICS', '30548', 'Closed', 'Tu Tuesday 3:55 PM–6:25 PM', 'WY 015', 'Yoosoon Chang', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'WYLIE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Advanced intensive study of a topic area in economics. Topics will vary.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 490', 'ADVANCED UNDERGRADUATE SEMINAR IN ECONOMICS', '36711', 'Closed', 'Th Thursday 3:55 PM–6:25 PM', 'WY 015', 'Rupal Kamdar', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'WYLIE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Advanced intensive study of a topic area in economics. Topics will vary.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 499', 'HONORS THESIS', '1470', 'Class Status', NULL, NULL, 'Volodymyr Lugovskyy', 4, NULL, 'Research', '3', NULL, ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Honors thesis research by special arrangement with an economics faculty mentor and the director of undergraduate studies.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 520', 'OPTIMIZATION THEORY IN ECONOMIC ANALYSIS', '1471', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 9:35 AM–12:05 PM', 'WY 329', 'Michael Kaganovich', 13, 'Lecture', 'Lecture', '3', 'WYLIE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Introduction to concepts and techniques of optimization theory applied in modern micro and macroeconomics. Theory and application of Lagrange multipliers, comparative statics analysis, valued functions and envelope theorems. Elements of dynamic programming and other methods of economic dynamics.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 520', 'OPTIMIZATION THEORY IN ECONOMIC ANALYSIS', '12387', 'Class Status', 'F Friday 8:30 AM–11:00 AM', 'WY 329', 'Qiulan Tao', 13, 'Laboratory', 'Lecture', '3', 'WYLIE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Introduction to concepts and techniques of optimization theory applied in modern micro and macroeconomics. Theory and application of Lagrange multipliers, comparative statics analysis, valued functions and envelope theorems. Elements of dynamic programming and other methods of economic dynamics.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 521', 'THEORY OF PRICES AND MARKETS 1', '1472', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 2:20 PM–3:35 PM', 'WY 329', 'Gustavo Torrens', 8, 'Lecture', 'Lecture', '3', 'WYLIE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Develops the methodology of economic analysis and teaches the tools and language of price theory. Fundamental elements of consumer theory, producer theory and economics of uncertainty. Emphasis on comparative statics and the duality theory. Topics on welfare analysis, the theory of price indices, quality of goods, revealed preferences, the theory of derived demand, expected utility theory, attitudes toward risk, and various measures of riskiness.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 521', 'THEORY OF PRICES AND MARKETS 1', '12388', 'Class Status', 'F Friday 11:30 AM–12:45 PM', 'BH 314', 'Jinzhe Xiang', 8, 'Laboratory', 'Lecture', '3', 'WYLIE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Develops the methodology of economic analysis and teaches the tools and language of price theory. Fundamental elements of consumer theory, producer theory and economics of uncertainty. Emphasis on comparative statics and the duality theory. Topics on welfare analysis, the theory of price indices, quality of goods, revealed preferences, the theory of derived demand, expected utility theory, attitudes toward risk, and various measures of riskiness.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 522', 'MACROECONOMIC THEORY I', '1473', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 12:45 PM–2:00 PM', 'WY 329', 'Yinxi Xie', 12, 'Lecture', 'Lecture', '3', 'WYLIE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Introductory course on macroeconomic dynamics; growth models and asset pricing theories are covered; also, endogenous growth theories, optimal growth problems, and competitive dynamic equilibrium models. Dynamic programming tools are introduced as needed. All models are cast in a discrete time setup; deterministic and stochastic theories are presented.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 522', 'MACROECONOMIC THEORY I', '12389', 'Class Status', 'F Friday 1:15 PM–2:30 PM', 'SE 245', 'Nayoung Lee', 12, 'Laboratory', 'Lecture', '3', 'WYLIE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Introductory course on macroeconomic dynamics; growth models and asset pricing theories are covered; also, endogenous growth theories, optimal growth problems, and competitive dynamic equilibrium models. Dynamic programming tools are introduced as needed. All models are cast in a discrete time setup; deterministic and stochastic theories are presented.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 530', 'INTERNATIONAL TRADE', '8338', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 11:10 AM–12:25 PM', 'BH 219', 'Ahmad Lashkaripour', 2, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'BALLANTINE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Introduction to theories of international trade (including topics like pattern of trade, gains from trade, testing trade theories) and analysis of trade policies (including topics like tariffs, quotas, and strategic trade policy).', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 571', 'ECONOMETRICS 1 - STATISTICAL FOUNDATIONS', '1474', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 8:00 AM–9:15 AM', 'WY 329', 'Joon Park', 13, 'Lecture', 'Lecture', '3', 'WYLIE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'The probability bases for statistical estimation and testing are introduced in the context of issues, theories, and data found in economics. The classical linear regression model is presented as the starting point for multivariate analyses in econometrics. Students work with various computer programs in and out of the scheduled class periods.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 571', 'ECONOMETRICS 1 - STATISTICAL FOUNDATIONS', '12390', 'Class Status', 'F Friday 3:00 PM–4:15 PM', 'BH 208', 'Sangmyung Ha', 13, 'Laboratory', 'Lecture', '3', 'WYLIE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'The probability bases for statistical estimation and testing are introduced in the context of issues, theories, and data found in economics. The classical linear regression model is presented as the starting point for multivariate analyses in econometrics. Students work with various computer programs in and out of the scheduled class periods.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 627', 'EXPERIMENTAL ECONOMICS', '11083', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 2:20 PM–3:35 PM', 'WY 125', 'Daniela Puzzello', 5, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'WYLIE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Focuses on the use of laboratory experimental methods in applied microeconomics. Specific application areas will include the analysis of resource allocation mechanisms for both private and public goods and individual choice under/uncertainty using both human and non-human subjects.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 671', 'ECONOMETRICS 3 - NONLINEAR AND SIMULTANEOUS MODELS', '12012', 'Class Status', 'M Monday 9:35 AM–12:05 PM', 'ED 1220', 'Keli Xu', 16, 'Lecture', 'Lecture', '3', 'WENDELL W. WRIGHT EDUCATION BU', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Introduction to econometric theory. Parameter estimation for single and multiple equation systems. Inference and hypothesis testing. Monte Carlo studies.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 671', 'ECONOMETRICS 3 - NONLINEAR AND SIMULTANEOUS MODELS', '12391', 'Class Status', 'Tu Tuesday 8:00 AM–9:15 AM', 'WY 329', 'Wansong Yang', 16, 'Laboratory', 'Lecture', '3', 'WENDELL W. WRIGHT EDUCATION BU', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Introduction to econometric theory. Parameter estimation for single and multiple equation systems. Inference and hypothesis testing. Monte Carlo studies.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 672', 'MACROECONOMETRICS', '6123', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 9:35 AM–10:50 AM', 'WY 329', 'Yoosoon Chang', 13, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'WYLIE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Advanced topics in econometrics. Estimation of dynamic equation systems. Spectrum analysis. Problems of design for large macro-econometric models.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('ECON-E 724', 'SEMINAR IN ECONOMIC THEORY', '1475', 'Class Status', 'Tu Tuesday 3:55 PM–6:25 PM', 'WY 015', 'Yoosoon Chang', 16, NULL, 'Seminar', '3', 'WYLIE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL, ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
